    pearls: ["CA 19-9 is NOT a screening test -- it is used for monitoring treatment response and detecting recurrence; Lewis antigen-negative patients (5-10%) will have falsely low CA 19-9 regardless of disease burden","Courvoisier sign (palpable, nontender gallbladder with painless jaundice) suggests malignant biliary obstruction (pancreatic head cancer) rather than gallstone disease","New-onset diabetes mellitus after age 50 without typical risk factors should raise suspicion for pancreatic cancer -- cancer may present as diabetes 1-3 years before diagnosis","Only 15-20% of pancreatic cancers are surgically resectable at diagnosis; the Whipple procedure (pancreaticoduodenectomy) has significant morbidity but is the only curative option","FOLFIRINOX provides superior survival over gemcitabine alone but is reserved for patients with ECOG 0-1 performance status due to significant toxicity","Pancreatic enzyme replacement therapy (PERT) must be taken WITH meals -- enzymes must mix with food to function; inadequate PERT leads to malabsorption, weight loss, and fat-soluble vitamin deficiency"],
